The IoT gateways market can be segmented based on three key parameters: component, connectivity technology, and end-use. The component segment includes hardware, software, and services. Hardware comprises physical devices such as sensors and processors, while software involves the programs that enable communication and data processing. Services include maintenance, support, and consulting related to IoT gateways. When considering connectivity technology, IoT gateways can either be wired or wireless, with options like Ethernet, Bluetooth, and Wi-Fi. Finally, the end-use segment covers various industries utilizing IoT gateways, including healthcare, automotive, retail, smart cities, and industrial applications.

